The paper deals with image captioning, which is a task in computer vision (CV). The approach involves generating natural language sentences (CL) that are grounded in entities detected in the image. The use of neural networks for captioning makes it relevant to machine learning (LG) and artificial intelligence (AI). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on standard datasets used in multimedia (MM) research.
